                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-154-victim1227 t18180909-154-viclabel838"></join>, in <placeName id="t18180909-154-crimeloc839">the Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-154-crimeloc839" type="placeName" value="the Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-154-crimeloc839" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-154-off836 t18180909-154-crimeloc839"></join>. On the 19th of August, about ten o'clock in the morning, the prisoner came to our shop, and asked for unlf a yard of cotton, at 1s. 6d. a yard, I served him. He then asked to see some silk handkerchiefs. I went to the window to get some, when I returned I observed the corner of the shawl between his coat and waistcoat, I went to the back-shop, and told Mr. Williams, I then went back and told the prisoner I had no handkerchiefs that would suit him. He was going to leave the shop, I followed him to the door, stopped him, and took the shawl from him. It was on the counter, close to him. I did not see him take it; this is it (producing it). I know it to be my master's.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I put it under my coat, and gave it to the gentleman when he asked for it.</p>
               <p>
